The paper deals with the problem of multicell coordinated beamforming with imperfect channel state information (CSI), which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper proposes a distributed optimization method using the alternating direction method of multipliers (ADMM), which is a popular technique in control and optimization of networked systems (cs.SY). The paper also presents simulation results to examine the effectiveness of the proposed method, which involves multimedia systems (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques.
